                <h3>About Lakshadweep</h3>
                <p class="para2">Lakshadweep Islands commonly known as coral paradise of India, a group of islands which is scattered in the Arabian Sea. This is one of the world's most spectacular tropical island systems, Lakshadweep is tucked away at 220-440Kms off cost of Kerala State of the Indian Peninsula. This archipelago consists of 36 sun-kissed islands comprises of 12 atolls, three reefs, five submerged banks and ten inhabited islands fringed by beautiful coral reefs and exotic marine life. The islands offer a precious heritage of ecology and culture. The unique feature of the Islands is its coral reef, making it a pristine leisure spot to come back. 4200 sq. kms of lagoon, rich in marine wealth, is spread over 36 islands in an area of 32 sq. kms.</p>
                <p id="para3">The underwater view at Lakshadweep is kaleidoscopic and breathtaking. Each island is fringed by snow white coral sands. The crystal clear water and the abundant marine life enhance the beauty of these islands. Against the vast expanse of the blue sea, the island looks like emeralds. The huge shallow calm lagoon on one side with wall like reef made of marine live coral boulders blocks the incoming swells of the outer sea. </p>
